				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$1.8\times {10}^{10}$$\end{document} cmHz1/2/W. These results suggest that the proposed heterostructure including a QD layer is promising for IR photodetectors that provide a high detectivity even at room temperature.
